data.chText: （国家、政党等的）结盟，联盟，同盟
data.enText: an agreement between countries, political parties, etc. to work together in order to achieve sth that they all want

data.chText: 社会民主党现在与绿党结成联盟。
data.enText: The Social Democrats are now in alliance with the Greens.
a group of people, political parties, etc. who work together in order to achieve sth that they all want

tr: the act of forming an alliance or confederation
a formal agreement establishing an association or alliance between nations or other groups to achieve a particular aim
an organization of people (or countries) involved in a pact or treaty
a connection based on kinship or marriage or common interest
example: the shifting alliances within a large family
their friendship constitutes a powerful bond between them

tr: the state of being allied or confederated

value.def: An alliance is a group of countries or political parties that are formally united and working together because they have similar aims.

example.ex: The two parties were still too much apart to form an alliance.
example.tran: 两党分歧甚大，还远未能结成同盟。

value.def: An alliance is a relationship in which two countries, political parties, or organizations work together for some purpose.

example.ex: What will be the effect of the alliance between IBM and Apple?...
example.tran: 若IBM公司和苹果公司联合将会有什么效果呢？

example.ex: They are now in a position to govern the state in alliance with either the Free Democrats or the Green Party.
example.tran: 他们现在可以选择与自由民主党人或绿党结盟来执掌国家政权。

gramarinfo.label: oft N <l>with/between</l> n, also <l>in</l> N <l>with</l> n

trans: 战略联盟；策略聯盟；战略同盟；策略联盟；企业战略联盟
